Monterey Peninsula Unified Dashboard DA Summary

Report Purpose

This report is created to assist Monterey Peninsula Unified in reflecting on the student groups whose indicators led to Differentiated Assistance.

Qualifying Groups

Differentiated Assistance is determined by the California Dashboard. Colors reflect the latest available status from 2023.

The graphic below shows the color for each student group for each indicator from the California 2023 Dashboard.

California Dashboard 2023

The table below displays which student groups qualified Monterey Peninsula Unified to be eligible for Differentiated Assistance. Moreover, for each student group it shows which Priority Areas and associated indicators met qualification criteria.

As a reminder, COEs must offer differentiated assistance to a school district if any student group meets the criteria for two or more LCFF priorities according to California Education Code Section 52071(c). Californiaâs System of Support

Status Details for all Indicators

These graphs represent all of the indicators from the Dashboard and show how each of the student groups performed. The vertical lines represent the cutpoints between different status levels.

Click here to display graphs

Historical Graphs for Eligible Groups

These graphs represent all of the indicators from Priority Areas that qualified the district. They included all qualifying subgroups on each graph, whether this was a qualifying indicator or not, as well as the All Students group for comparisons.

Status Needed to Exit DA in 2023

This section estimates the limits for relevant indicators to receive an orange or higher color next year on the 2024 Dashboard. The thresholds below are based on the 5x5 grids last approved by the State Board of Education and the number of students in the 2023 calculation. State policies may change and the student counts may shift.
